Encryption fixed, I derped so hard that I put the socket tree reader method in the wrong class and was staring at the broken code for days wondering why I got all these weird values >.<
Progress can be followed in my commits for shirioko/WhatsApiNet. I have to update the inbound and outbound node syntax, they're using a new format. E.g.:
Message:
```xml
RECVD: <message from="316********@s.whatsapp.net" id="130353783428798361-0" type
="text" t="1390904800" notify="Max">
RECVD:   <body>Huewhuehue</body>
RECVD: </message>
```
Typing/paused:
```xml
RECVD: <chatstate from="316********@s.whatsapp.net">
RECVD:   <composing></composing>
RECVD: </chatstate>

RECVD: <chatstate from="316********@s.whatsapp.net">
RECVD:   <paused></paused>
RECVD: </chatstate>
```
And lots more

Great news, superb work man
